A Python module that permits to parse Json based configuration files, wrapping my Json parser in the library libjparse ( available in this github account ).

* Quickstart:

import jsonPy

try:
        jsonPy.open("/Users/bg/_Sorgenti/_Json/_JsonPy_LY_hg/test/jsons/sample.null.json")
        jsonPy.getStringValueByPath("xxxroot.menu.title")
except jsonPy.JsonPyError,e:
        print "Exception catched"
        print e.args

* Outuput:

  Exception catched
 ('Invalid Json node',)

* Note:

Beta version only few features of libjparse are available: all the features will be added as soon as possible.
